      "creatureType": "",
      "blurb": "",
      "publicNotes": "<h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p><strong>Role (B26 + random-encounter wanderers):</strong> Kazavon's court jesters — Pegg halfling-short with a peg leg scavenged from chair-wood, Loute over seven feet with arms to mid-calf — executed by having leather masks <em>sewn over their heads</em> and hung from hooks above the castle gate to suffocate slowly while the troops applauded. Their ghosts still wear the costumes and masks. They rush at the living gesticulating wildly, 'trying to tell the PCs something' — there is nothing to tell; only the pantomime's damage. Lull, then corrupting touch if attacked; they fight until destroyed — they never did know when to quit.</p>",
      "privateNotes": ""
    },
